<p class="article-lead">A perfume box has three jobs: protect the bottle, carry required information and present the brand. Structural design should begin with the actual bottle and cap, not a guessed dimension.</p><h2>Control movement</h2><p>Choose an insert that supports the bottle without marking its finish. Consider orientation, removal force and vibration during transport. Heavy caps and irregular glass need more than a visually attractive cavity.</p><h2>Prepare artwork for production</h2><p>Use the final dieline, include bleed and safe areas, and reserve space for ingredients, responsible-party information, volume, warnings, batch coding and barcode as applicable. Review foil, embossing and dark solid colors on physical material.</p><p>For e-commerce, test the retail box inside its shipping protection. A beautiful carton that collapses or allows glass-to-glass movement is not production-ready.</p>
